'''Mateo Kovačić''' ({{IPA|hr|matěo kǒʋatʃitɕ}};<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=e1tnXBk%3D&keyword=Sv.|title=Màtej|quote=Matèo|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|access-date=17 March 2018|language=sh|archive-date=1 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301183838/http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=e1tnXBk%3D&keyword=Sv.|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=ellgUBQ%3D|title=kòvati|quote=Kòvačič|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|access-date=17 March 2018|language=sh|archive-date=17 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191217035538/http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=ellgUBQ=|url-status=live}}</ref> born 6 May 1994) is a <!-- Do not add Austrian born or Croatian! Per MOS:BLPLEAD, MOS:CONTEXTBIO, WP:MOSETHNICITY, and WP:FOOTY, unless ethnicity contributes to notability, it should not be mentioned in the lede. It should be left ambiguous, as he was born in a nation different than that which he represents internationally. --> professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] for {{English football updater|ManchesC}} club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

Kovačić began his professional career with [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] at the age of 16, with whom he won two consecutive [[Prva HNL]] titles, before joining [[Inter Milan]] in 2013. In 2015, he moved to [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]], where he won nine trophies, including three [[UEFA Champions League]] titles between 2016 and 2018. He subsequently joined [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], where he won the [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]], a fourth Champions League title, the [[2021 UEFA Super Cup|UEFA Super Cup]] and the [[2021 FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Cup]], as well as being named [[Chelsea Player of the Year]] for the [[2019–20 Chelsea F.C. season|2019–20 season]].  He joined [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in the summer of 2023, and won the Premier League with them in his [[2023–24 Premier League|first season]].

Born in [[Austria]], Kovačić played for Croatia at multiple youth levels before making his debut for the senior national team in 2013. He has represented the nation at the [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]], [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]] and [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]s, as well as the [[UEFA Euro 2016|2016]], [[UEFA Euro 2020|2020]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024|2024 UEFA European Championship]]s, reaching the [[2018 FIFA World Cup final|2018 World Cup final]] and [[2023 UEFA Nations League final]].

==Club career==
===Youth career===
Kovačić began playing at an early age at the local [[LASK]]'s academy.<ref name="zidak">{{cite news |last=Židak |first=Tomislav |date=22 November 2010 |title=Meteor Kovačić: Svi su ludi za dječakom koji je već sa 13 igrao zrelo kao nekad Maradona |url=http://www.jutarnji.hr/mateo-kovacic-kao-maradona--modric--pele---/905740/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022014811/http://www.jutarnji.hr/mateo-kovacic-kao-maradona--modric--pele---/905740/ |archive-date=22 October 2012 |access-date=22 November 2010 |work=[[Jutarnji list]] |language=hr}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web |last1=Miličić |first1=Dubravko |last2=Tironi |first2=Hrvoje |date=18 November 2020 |title=Ministrant od 45 milijuna eura |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/ministrant-od-45-milijuna-eura-slomio-sam-nogu-s-14-godina-a-sa-16-igrao-za-seniore-dinama-728811 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201118101155/https://www.24sata.hr/sport/ministrant-od-45-milijuna-eura-slomio-sam-nogu-s-14-godina-a-sa-16-igrao-za-seniore-dinama-728811 |archive-date=18 November 2020 |access-date=19 November 2020 |website=24sata |language=hr}}</ref> In 2007, when Kovačić was 13, he was spotted by scouts from several prominent European clubs, including [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], [[Inter Milan]], [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] and [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], but his family opted to move to [[Zagreb]] instead, where he joined the [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb Academy|academy]] of Croatian club [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 October 2022 |title=Kovacic complimentary of Milan: "A great opponent, with a great history" |url=https://sempremilan.com/kovacic-chelsea-milan-great-opponent-history |access-date=15 April 2025 |website=SempreMilan}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Cigoj |first=Mark |date=2 February 2013 |title=Cijela istina o Mateu Kovačiću |url=http://www.jutarnji.hr/mateo-kovacic--kako-je-stvoren-igrac-od-100-milijuna-kuna/1082758/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130204205731/http://www.jutarnji.hr/mateo-kovacic--kako-je-stvoren-igrac-od-100-milijuna-kuna/1082758/ |archive-date=4 February 2013 |access-date=1 June 2014 |work=Jutarnji list |language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=croatiaweek |date=29 May 2021 |title=Mateo Kovačić equals Luka Modrić's Croatian Champions League title record |url=https://www.croatiaweek.com/mateo-kovacic-equals-luka-modrics-croatian-champions-league-title-record/ |access-date=15 April 2025 |website=Croatia Week}}</ref>

In 2009, at the age of 15, Kovačić suffered a serious injury. His leg was broken and he could not even stand on it for the first four months after the injury. After a lengthy recovery, he finally returned to the team on 31 May 2010, appearing in the last match of the [[Prva HNL Academy|Croatian under-17 academy league]], in a [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] 5–0 win against [[RNK Split]] under-17s.<ref name="kadeti">{{cite news |last=Rupnik |first=Borna |date=31 May 2010 |title=Kadeti Dinama za naslov prestigli Hajduk |url=http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/398143/nogomet-1-hnl/kadeti-dinama-za-naslov-prestigli-hajduk |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102111655/http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/398143/nogomet-1-hnl/kadeti-dinama-za-naslov-prestigli-hajduk/ |archive-date=2 November 2012 |access-date=22 November 2010 |publisher=[[Sportnet.hr|Sportnet]] |language=hr}}</ref>

===Dinamo Zagreb===
Kovačić started training with the club's senior squad under manager, [[Vahid Halilhodžić]], four months later, on 6 October 2010,<ref name="vahid">{{cite news |date=6 October 2010 |title=Mateo Kovačić od danas trenira sa seniorima Dinama: Plaši me nadimak Hrvatski Messi |url=http://sportske.jutarnji.hr/mateo-kovacic-od-danas-trenira-sa-seniorima-dinama--plasi-me-nadimak-hrvatski-messi/892846/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101019005155/http://sportske.jutarnji.hr/mateo-kovacic-od-danas-trenira-sa-seniorima-dinama--plasi-me-nadimak-hrvatski-messi/892846/ |archive-date=19 October 2010 |access-date=20 November 2010 |newspaper=[[Sportske novosti]] |language=hr}}</ref> but continued to appear for the club in academy league matches during October. Later that month, it was reported by the local sports daily, ''[[Sportske novosti]]'', that [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]'s chief scout, Steve Rowley, had arrived in Zagreb to watch him perform in under-17 matches against [[HNK Cibalia]] and [[NK Zagreb]].<ref name="sportske">{{cite news |date=29 October 2010 |title=Arsenal došao po Matea Kovačića, Dinamo našao novo čudo od djeteta&nbsp;— Miralema Ramića |url=http://sportske.jutarnji.hr/arsenal-dosao-po-matea-kovacica--dinamo-nasao-novo-cudo-od-djeteta---miralema-ramica/899213/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029200218/http://sportske.jutarnji.hr/arsenal-dosao-po-matea-kovacica--dinamo-nasao-novo-cudo-od-djeteta---miralema-ramica/899213/ |archive-date=29 October 2013 |access-date=22 November 2010 |newspaper=Sportske novosti |language=hr}}</ref> Kovačić had his professional league debut in the [[2010–11 Croatian First Football League|2010–11 Prva HNL]] away match against [[NK Hrvatski Dragovoljac|Hrvatski Dragovoljac]] on 20 November 2010, in which he scored Dinamo's fourth goal in their 6–0 win.<ref name="debut">{{cite news |last=Rupnik |first=Borna |date=20 November 2010 |title=I Kovačić strijelac u Dinamovoj šestici |url=http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/407740/nogomet-1-hnl/i-kovacic-strijelac-u-dinamovoj-sestici |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025045603/http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/407740/nogomet-1-hnl/i-kovacic-strijelac-u-dinamovoj-sestici/ |archive-date=25 October 2012 |access-date=20 November 2010 |publisher=Sportnet |language=hr}}</ref> This made him the youngest goalscorer in the history of the league, at the age of 16 years and 198 days, breaking the record set only a week earlier by [[Dino Špehar]] who had scored for [[NK Osijek]] at the age of 16 years and 278 days on 13 November 2010.<ref name="record">{{cite news |date=20 November 2010 |title=Mateo Kovačić najmlađi je strijelac Prve HNL |url=http://www.tportal.hr/sport/TcomPrvaHNL/97374/Mateo-Kovacic-najmladi-je-strijelac-Prve-HNL.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930181931/http://www.tportal.hr/sport/TcomPrvaHNL/97374/Mateo-Kovacic-najmladi-je-strijelac-Prve-HNL.html |archive-date=30 September 2015 |access-date=20 November 2010 |publisher=TPortal |language=hr}}</ref><ref name="spehar">{{cite news |last=Plavčić |first=Mario |date=13 November 2010 |title=Špehar spasio bijelo-plave |url=http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/407385/nogomet-1-hnl/spehar-spasio-bijelo-plave |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024131941/http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/407385/nogomet-1-hnl/spehar-spasio-bijelo-plave/ |archive-date=24 October 2012 |access-date=22 November 2010 |work=Sportnet.hr |language=hr}}</ref> In his first senior season with [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] he appeared in seven matches, making a contribution in winning the league title.{{citation needed|date=April 2023}}

In the [[2011–12 Croatian First Football League|2011–12]] season, Kovačić rapidly established himself as a first-team regular. He played mainly in the position of left midfielder in 4–2–3–1 system. Early in the season, he helped the team reach the [[2011–12 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group D|group stage]] of [[2011–12 UEFA Champions League|the season's UEFA Champions League]] for the first time in 12 years. Being only 17 years old, he appeared in the starting line-up of Dinamo's first group match against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]. He finished his first European season with Dinamo by scoring a goal against [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] in the last game of the group stage in Zagreb and thus became the second youngest ever scorer in the Champions League. In the domestic league, he was a regular starter, appearing in 25 league matches and scoring five goals in the process. During a league match against [[NK Lučko]], he became the youngest player to [[Captain (association football)|captain]] Dinamo, when taking the captaincy from [[Leandro Cufré]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Kvačić najmlađi kapetan u Dnamovoj povijesti |url=http://www.tportal.hr/sport/prvaliga/145385/Kovacic-najmladi-kapetan-Dinama-u-povijesti.html#.UQm78x32_Wo |date=27 August 2011 |work=Tportal.hr |access-date=31 January 2013 |archive-date=4 October 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004223151/http://www.tportal.hr/sport/prvaliga/145385/Kovacic-najmladi-kapetan-Dinama-u-povijesti.html#.UQm78x32_Wo |url-status=live }}</ref> It was another successful season for him in domestic competitions as he appeared in 32 domestic league and cup matches during that season, helping Dinamo to win their seventh consecutive league title. He also scored in the [[2012 Croatian Football Cup final|2012 Croatian Cup final]] against Osijek at [[Stadion Maksimir]]. In December 2011, he was named [[Croatian Footballer of the Year#Hope of the Year|Croatian Football Hope of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web |date=31 December 2011 |title=Kovačiću trofej Nada godine: Liga prvaka je bila uživancija |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/kovacicu-trofej-nada-godine-liga-prvaka-je-bila-uzivancija-248104 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029200325/http://www.24sata.hr/nogomet/kovacicu-trofej-nada-godine-liga-prvaka-je-bila-uzivancija-248104 |archive-date=29 October 2013 |access-date=31 December 2011 |website=24sata.hr |language=hr}}</ref>

In the beginning of [[2012–13 Croatian First Football League|2012–13]] season, he suffered a metatarsal bone injury that caused him to miss several games on the club's qualifying road to another Champions League. He returned just in time to play in Dinamo's first [[2012–13 UEFA Champions League|2012–13 Champions League]] game against [[FC Porto|Porto]]. Kovačić played in all six Dinamo Zagreb's matches in the [[2012–13 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group A|2012–13 Champions League group stage]], against Porto, [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] and [[FC Dynamo Kyiv|Dynamo Kyiv]]. He continued to impress with his mature performances at a young age during the first half of the season. In October 2012, he was nominated for [[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]], an award given by sports journalists to a young player from Europe perceived to have been the most impressive during a season.<ref>{{cite web |date=30 October 2012 |title=Kovačić kandidat za prestižnu nagradu "Golden Boy 2012." |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/kovacic-kandidat-za-prestiznu-nagradu-golden-boy-2012-287471 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121101034833/http://www.24sata.hr/nogomet/kovacic-kandidat-za-prestiznu-nagradu-golden-boy-2012-287471 |archive-date=1 November 2012 |access-date=31 January 2013 |website=24sata.hr |language=hr}}</ref> During the season's winter break, Dinamo's board threw away the speculations about Kovačić leaving the club in the near future by saying they are building a new team around him and another rising star, [[Alen Halilović]].<ref>{{cite web |date=15 December 2012 |title=Kovačića i Halilovića nećemo prodati! |url=http://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/dinamo-sporting-nam-se-nije-javio-kovacica-i-halilovica-necemo-prodati/652404.aspx |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130118173736/http://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/dinamo-sporting-nam-se-nije-javio-kovacica-i-halilovica-necemo-prodati/652404.aspx |archive-date=18 January 2013 |access-date=8 April 2013 |publisher=index.hr |language=hr}}</ref>

===Inter Milan===
====2012–13 season====
[[File:Mateo Kovacic.jpg|thumb|upright|Kovačić playing for [[Inter Milan]] in 2013]]
On 31 January 2013, Kovačić agreed to a transfer to [[Serie A]] club Inter Milan.<ref>{{Cite news |date=18 August 2015 |title=Mateo Kovacic: Real Madrid sign Inter Milan midfielder |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/33979878 |access-date=15 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> The deal was worth €15&nbsp;million in total, with €11&nbsp;million paid immediately and €4&nbsp;million if Inter were to qualify for the Champions League.<ref>{{cite news |last=Taidelli |first=Luca |date=2 February 2013 |title=Inter, Kovacic da 10, Maglia e calcio senza paura |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/02-02-2013/inter-kovacic-10-video-maglia-calcio-senza-paura-914107775713.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140809100502/http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/02-02-2013/inter-kovacic-10-video-maglia-calcio-senza-paura-914107775713.shtml |archive-date=9 August 2014 |access-date=29 August 2014 |newspaper=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]] |language=it}}</ref> He made his Inter Milan debut three days later on 3 February, coming on as a half-time [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a [[2012–13 Serie A]] match against [[S.S. Robur Siena|Siena]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Clari |first=Valerio |date=3 February 2013 |title=Siena-Inter 3–1, Stramaccioni affonda sotto i gol di Sestu e Emeghara |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Siena/03-02-2013/siena-inter-3-1-male-nerazzurri-sestu-emeghara-dominano--914124870634.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130411015155/http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Siena/03-02-2013/siena-inter-3-1-male-nerazzurri-sestu-emeghara-dominano--914124870634.shtml |archive-date=11 April 2013 |access-date=8 April 2013 |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=it}}</ref> On 14 February, Kovačić made his European debut before the home crowd at [[San Siro]] in a [[2012–13 UEFA Europa League]] match against [[CFR Cluj]]. He provided the winning [[Assist (association football)|assist]] for [[Rodrigo Palacio]], who made it 2–0 for Inter, impressing the crowd with his performance, and was given standing ovations while being substituted off in the 89th minute.<ref>{{cite news |last=Clari |first=Valerio |date=15 February 2013 |title=Inter-Cluj 2–0: Doppio Palacio, ottimo Kovacic, ma infortunio per Milito |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/14-02-2013/inter-cluj-2-0-doppio-palacio-ottimo-kovacic-ma-infortunio-milito-923391317.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221034546/http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/14-02-2013/inter-cluj-2-0-doppio-palacio-ottimo-kovacic-ma-infortunio-milito-923391317.shtml |archive-date=21 December 2014 |access-date=29 August 2014 |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=it}}</ref>

Kovačić made his first domestic league start for Inter in the next round of Serie A in a 1–4 away loss against [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]]. In the round of 16 of the Europa League, Inter was drawn to play against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]]. After a 3–0 loss in London, Inter needed a 4–0 win in [[Milan]] to proceed to the next round. The match ended in a 4–1 win for Inter after the match went into extra time, with Kovačić playing as a starter. He impressed with his composure and playmaking ability, once again receiving ovations by the fans.<ref>{{cite news |last=Clari |first=Valerio |date=14 March 2013 |title=Inter-Tottenham 4–1, Cassano da applausi, ma non-basta: Spurs ai quarti |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/14-03-2013/europa-league-inter-tottenham-92474067493.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924144125/http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/14-03-2013/europa-league-inter-tottenham-92474067493.shtml |archive-date=24 September 2015 |access-date=29 August 2014 |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=it}}</ref> Inter manager [[Andrea Stramaccioni]] hailed his performances on several occasions, describing him as a "star for the future".<ref>{{cite web |last=Mondal |first=Subhankar |date=18 March 2013 |title=Inter Milan coach Andrea Stramaccioni hails Mateo Kovacic |url=http://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/inter-milan/news/stramaccioni-hails-kovacic_74900.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130331002646/http://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/inter-milan/news/stramaccioni-hails-kovacic_74900.html |archive-date=31 March 2013 |access-date=8 April 2013 |publisher=Sportsmole.co.uk}}</ref>

On 30 March, Kovačić was a starter in his first ''[[Derby d'Italia]]'' against Juventus at San Siro. The derby ended in a 1–2 win for Juventus, with Kovačić starting the action that resulted in Rodrigo Palacio's 1–1 equaliser.<ref>{{cite news |last=Schianchi |first=Andrea |date=31 March 2013 |title=Inter-Juve. Con Kovacic e Pirlo, precisione al potere |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/SerieA/Bigmatch/31-03-2013/inter-juve-kovacic-pirlo-precisione-potere-92754618835.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130403080025/http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/SerieA/Bigmatch/31-03-2013/inter-juve-kovacic-pirlo-precisione-potere-92754618835.shtml |archive-date=3 April 2013 |access-date=31 March 2013 |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=it}}</ref> Kovačić was a starter in Inter's next Serie A match, a 0–2 away win against [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]], as well as in their surprising 3–4 loss to [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]] at San Siro, where he provided an assist for [[Ricky Álvarez]]'s goal.<ref>{{cite news |last=Gerna |first=Jacopo |date=4 April 2013 |title=Sampdoria-Inter 0–2, decide la doppietta di Palacio |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Sampdoria/03-04-2013/solito-palacio-stende-samp-inter-stramaccioni-respirano-92805504703.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150805164758/http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Sampdoria/03-04-2013/solito-palacio-stende-samp-inter-stramaccioni-respirano-92805504703.shtml |archive-date=5 August 2015 |access-date=29 August 2014 |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Clari |first=Valerio |date=8 April 2013 |title=Inter-Atalanta 3–4, tripletta di Denis fra errori, botte e rimonte |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/07-04-2013/inter-atalanta-3-4-tripletta-denis-errori-botte-rimonte-92875894700.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130815072224/http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Squadre/Inter/07-04-2013/inter-atalanta-3-4-tripletta-denis-errori-botte-rimonte-92875894700.shtml |archive-date=15 August 2013 |access-date=29 August 2013 |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=it}}</ref> By the end of the second half of the season, he was a starter in all of the club's Serie A fixtures, as Inter finished in disappointing ninth place on the Serie A table. In May, he was given the "Gentleman Revelation of the Year" award, awarded by Inter fans.<ref>{{cite news |last=Velluzzi |first=Francesco |date=9 May 2013 |title=Zanetti fa 13: vince ancora il Gentleman Kovacic e De Sciglio i migliori giovani |url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2013/maggio/09/Zanetti_vince_ancora_Gentleman_Kovacic_ga_0_20130509_a099669c-b86c-11e2-bc10-72b41185888f.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303201009/http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2013/maggio/09/Zanetti_vince_ancora_Gentleman_Kovacic_ga_0_20130509_a099669c-b86c-11e2-bc10-72b41185888f.shtml |archive-date=3 March 2016 |access-date=29 August 2013 |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=it}}</ref>

====2013–2015====
Kovačić missed most of the pre-season training with the squad due to series of small injuries,<ref>{{cite web |title=Kovacic out seven days, will miss first friendly match |url=http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/07/16/kovacic-out-seven-days-will-miss-first-friendly-match/ |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=16 July 2013 |publisher=fedenerazzurra.com |access-date=31 January 2014 |archive-date=4 February 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140204041724/http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/07/16/kovacic-out-seven-days-will-miss-first-friendly-match/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Kovacic to miss another 10 days, out against Hamburg and Chelsea |url=http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/07/27/cds-kovacic-to-miss-another-10-days-out-against-hamburg-and-chelsea/ |newspaper=Corriere dello Sport |date=27 July 2013 |publisher=fedenerazzurra.com |access-date=31 January 2014 |archive-date=4 February 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140204041721/http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/07/27/cds-kovacic-to-miss-another-10-days-out-against-hamburg-and-chelsea/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> and made his comeback just few days before the first official match of the new season, a Coppa Italia match against [[A.S. Cittadella|Cittadella]] at Stadio Giuseppe Meazza.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kovacic ready to return versus Cittadella |url=http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/08/13/kovacic-ready-to-return-versus-cittadella/ |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |date=13 August 2013 |publisher=fedenerazzurra.com |access-date=1 February 2014 |archive-date=4 February 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140204041843/http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/08/13/kovacic-ready-to-return-versus-cittadella/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> During the pre-season interviews, new Inter manager [[Walter Mazzarri]] hinted Kovačić would be given a new role on the pitch, a role similar to [[Marek Hamšík]]'s in Napoli.<ref>{{cite web |date=11 July 2013 |title=Mazzarri: "Non vendo fumo, Kovacic alla Hamsik" |url=http://it.eurosport.yahoo.com/notizie/calcio-in-trentino-mazzarri-non-vendo-fumo-kovacic-110123735.html |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224144135/http://it.eurosport.yahoo.com/notizie/calcio-in-trentino-mazzarri-non-vendo-fumo-kovacic-110123735.html |archive-date=24 February 2014 |access-date=31 January 2014 |publisher=Eurosport |language=it}}</ref> During the first half of the season, Kovačić played regularly, although he struggled with adjusting to his new tactical role.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mazzola: "Kovacic is still not ready" |url=http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/10/31/mazzola-kovacic-is-still-not-ready/ |work=Novastadio |date=31 October 2013 |publisher=fedenerazzurra.com |access-date=1 February 2014 |archive-date=4 February 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140204041837/http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/10/31/mazzola-kovacic-is-still-not-ready/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> Kovačić made his first assist of the season in the match against [[A.S. Livorno Calcio|Livorno]], when he delivered an assist for [[Yuto Nagatomo]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Zanetti was the main event but everyone forgot about Kovacic |url=http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/11/10/zanetti-was-the-main-event-but-everyone-forgot-about-kovacic/ |website=Sky Italia |date=10 November 2013 |publisher=fedenerazzurra.com |access-date=1 February 2014 |archive-date=4 February 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140204041840/http://fedenerazzurra.com/2013/11/10/zanetti-was-the-main-event-but-everyone-forgot-about-kovacic/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> Unlike the previous season under manager Andrea Stramaccioni, Kovačić was not a regular starter during the 2013–14 season. In 32 Serie A matches played, he started only 14, playing the entire 90 minutes on just eight occasions.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ibrulj |first1=Saša |title=Can Mateo Kovacic Become a Regular at Inter Milan This Season? |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2136193-can-mateo-kovacic-become-a-regular-at-inter-milan-this-season |publisher=bleacherreport.com |access-date=15 September 2014 |archive-date=15 September 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915163308/http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2136193-can-mateo-kovacic-become-a-regular-at-inter-milan-this-season |url-status=live }}</ref> He received the chance to restore his confidence towards the end of the season, as he was Mazzarri's first-choice in the midfield in Inter's last six matches.{{citation needed|date=April 2023}}

After being subjected to persistent transfer speculation over the summer, in September 2014, Kovačić was offered a contract extension until 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kemp |first1=Jamie |title=Barcelona bid for Mateo Kovačić rejected by Inter Milan |url=http://www.insidespanishfootball.com/123331/barcelona-bid-for-mateo-kovacic-rejected-by-inter-milan/ |website=insidespanishfootball |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915184540/http://www.insidespanishfootball.com/123331/barcelona-bid-for-mateo-kovacic-rejected-by-inter-milan/ |archive-date=15 September 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Barcelona Transfer News: Dani Alves to Leave in 2015, Mateo Kovacic Bid Revealed |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2184122-barcelona-transfer-news-dani-alves-to-leave-in-2015-mateo-kovacic-bid-revealed |publisher=bleacherreport.com |access-date=15 September 2014 |archive-date=15 September 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915163305/http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2184122-barcelona-transfer-news-dani-alves-to-leave-in-2015-mateo-kovacic-bid-revealed |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Inter to lock down Kovacic and Icardi until 2019 |date=10 September 2014 |url=http://forzaitalianfootball.com/2014/09/inter-to-lock-down-kovacic-and-icardi-until-2019/ |access-date=15 September 2014 |archive-date=15 September 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915184510/http://forzaitalianfootball.com/2014/09/inter-to-lock-down-kovacic-and-icardi-until-2019/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He started the season in strong fashion, scoring a [[Hat-trick (association football)|hat-trick]] in the second leg of the [[2014–15 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round#Play-off round|Europa League play-off round]] against [[Stjarnan men's football|Stjarnan]] on 28 August.<ref>{{cite news |date=28 August 2014 |title=Inter, tutto facile: Stjarnan battuto 6–0 |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Inter/28-08-2014/inter-tutto-facile-stjarnan-battuto-6-0-90282903797.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140829223740/http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Inter/28-08-2014/inter-tutto-facile-stjarnan-battuto-6-0-90282903797.shtml |archive-date=29 August 2014 |access-date=29 August 2014 |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=28 August 2014 |title=Mazzarri promuove Kovacic 'Cresce nel modo giusto' |url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Inter/28-08-2014/inter-mazzarri-kovacic-sta-crescendmodo-giusto-90285455372.shtml |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20140915074213/http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Inter/28-08-2014/inter-mazzarri-kovacic-sta-crescendmodo-giusto-90285455372.shtml |archive-date=15 September 2014 |access-date=29 August 2014 |newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=it}}</ref> He scored his first league goal for Inter and assisted twice in a 7–0 win over [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] on 14 September 2014.<ref>{{cite news |title=Inter Milan 7–0 Sassuolo |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/29198823 |access-date=14 September 2014 |website=BBC Sport |date=14 September 2014 |archive-date=15 September 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915135537/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29198823 |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored the club's only goal in a 1–1 away draw with [[Palermo F.C.|Palermo]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Mateo Kovacic scored his second goal in as many matches as Inter Milan fought back from a goal down to draw with Palermo. |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29277861 |date=21 September 2014 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=28 September 2014 |archive-date=24 September 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924061010/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29277861 |url-status=live }}</ref> He also scored the opening goal in a 2–0 win against [[A.C. ChievoVerona|ChievoVerona]] and scored a wonder goal in a 2–2 drawn against Lazio. On 6 January 2015, he was sent-off in a 1–1 draw with Juventus for a foul on [[Stephan Lichtsteiner]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Juventus 1–1 Inter Milan |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30687617 |access-date=7 January 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=6 January 2014 |archive-date=7 January 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150107084021/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30687617 |url-status=live }}</ref> Three days later, Kovačić renewed his contract with Inter until June 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kovačić extends Inter deal till 2019 |url=http://www.inter.it/en/news/47286 |access-date=9 January 2015 |publisher=Inter Milan |date=9 January 2014 |archive-date=9 January 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150109231559/http://www.inter.it/en/news/47286 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

===Real Madrid===
[[File:Shahter-Reak M 2015 (14).jpg|thumb|upright|Kovačić playing for [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in 2015]]
On 16 August 2015, Inter manager [[Roberto Mancini]] confirmed the club was forced to sell Kovačić to [[La Liga]] club Real Madrid due to [[UEFA Financial Fair Play Regulations]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.inter.it/en/news/48790 |title=Mancini: "We had our chances" |date=16 August 2015 |publisher=Inter Milan |access-date=18 August 2015 |archive-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229183658/https://www.inter.it/en/news/48790 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Real Madrid also confirmed the transfer two days later, announcing Kovačić had signed a six-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2015/08/official-announcement-mateo-kova%C4%8Di%C4%87 |title=Official announcement: Mateo Kovačić |date=18 August 2015 |publisher=Real Madrid CF |access-date=18 August 2015 |archive-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229215244/https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2015/08/official-announcement-mateo-kova%C4%8Di%C4%87 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/aug/16/real-madrid-internazionale-mateo-kovacic |title=Real Madrid agree €32m fee with Internazionale to sign Mateo Kovacic |last1=Christenson |first1=Marcus |last2=Romano |first2=Fabrizio |date=16 August 2015 |access-date=28 August 2015 |work=The Guardian |archive-date=31 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831042421/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/aug/16/real-madrid-internazionale-mateo-kovacic |url-status=live |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> The transfer fee was €29&nbsp;million, according to Inter's financial filings.<ref>F.C. Internazionale Milano S.p.A. ''bilancio'' (financial report and accounts) on 30 June 2015 PDF purchased from [[Camera di Commercio, Industria, Agricoltura e Artigianato|CCIAA]] (in Italian)</ref> On 19 August, Kovačić was unveiled as a new player by Real Madrid at the [[Santiago Bernabéu Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2015/08/kovacic-being-at-the-biggest-club-in-the-world-is-really-special |title=Kovacic: "Being at the biggest club in the world is really special" |date=19 August 2015 |publisher=Real Madrid CF |access-date=19 August 2015 |archive-date=21 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150821001613/http://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2015/08/kovacic-being-at-the-biggest-club-in-the-world-is-really-special |url-status=live }}</ref> Kovačić became the fifth Croatian player, after [[Robert Prosinečki]], [[Davor Šuker]], [[Robert Jarni]] and [[Luka Modrić]], to join Real Madrid.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kovačić peti Hrvat u dresu Kraljevskog kluba |url=http://sport.hrt.hr/295444/kovacic-peti-hrvat-u-dresu-kraljevskog-kluba |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160105090426/http://sport.hrt.hr/295444/kovacic-peti-hrvat-u-dresu-kraljevskog-kluba |archive-date=5 January 2016 |access-date=3 November 2015 |website=HRT Sport |publisher=Hrt}}</ref>

Four days after his presentation, he made his debut as a 70th-minute substitute for [[Isco]] as Real Madrid began the [[2015–16 La Liga]] with a 0–0 draw away to [[Sporting de Gijón|Sporting Gijón]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Sporting spoil Benítez debut |url=http://www.marca.com/en/2015/08/23/en/football/real_madrid/1440360649.html |access-date=23 August 2015 |work=Marca|location=Spain |date=23 August 2015 |archive-date=23 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180623165834/http://www.marca.com/en/2015/08/23/en/football/real_madrid/1440360649.html |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored his first goal in an 8–0 home win over [[Malmö FF]] on 8 December 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0228-0e92cb1b045d-13a834dc2ded-1000--ronaldo-rampant-as-madrid-put-eight-past-malmo/ |title=Ronaldo rampant as Madrid put eight past Malmö |publisher=UEFA |date=8 December 2015 |access-date=9 December 2015 |archive-date=23 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923095755/http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2016/matches/round=2000634/match=2015746/postmatch/report/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref> He made 34 appearances in his first season at Real Madrid.{{citation needed|date=April 2023}} In the opening months of the season, he was used quite regularly by then Real Madrid manager [[Rafael Benítez]], playing in almost every midfield position there is&nbsp;– sometimes central, sometimes wide, sometimes further forward. However, after [[Zinedine Zidane]] replaced Benítez in early January, Kovačić's appearances became increasingly infrequent. With the Frenchman preferring to use a very defined starting 11 whenever possible instead of the more specific-lineups-for-specific-opponents approach employed by his predecessor, there was little room for Kovačić. He made eight appearances and scored one goal as Real Madrid won the [[2015–16 UEFA Champions League|2015–16 Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/022d-0e957c5979eb-37493cb53cd0-1000--spot-on-real-madrid-defeat-atletico-in-final-again/ |title=Spot-on Real Madrid defeat Atlético in final again |date=28 May 2016 |publisher=UEFA |access-date=29 May 2016 |archive-date=10 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180110225552/http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2016/matches/round=2000638/match=2015789/postmatch/report/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

Kovačić scored his first Liga goal on 29 January 2017 in a 3–0 win over [[Real Sociedad]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38719239|title=Real Madrid 3–0 Real Sociedad|website=BBC Sport|date=29 January 2017|access-date=13 February 2018|archive-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229211126/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38719239|url-status=live}}</ref> He was a part-time starter when Madrid won the [[2016–17 La Liga]]<ref>{{cite web |date=21 May 2017 |title=El Real Madrid, campeón de LaLiga Santander 2016/17 |url=http://www.laliga.es/noticias/real-madrid-campeon-de-laliga-santander-2016-17 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712180825/http://www.laliga.es/noticias/real-madrid-campeon-de-laliga-santander-2016-17 |archive-date=12 July 2019 |access-date=22 May 2017 |publisher=Liga Nacional de Fútbol Profesional}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39926301|title=Real Madrid win La Liga title with victory at Malaga|website=BBC Sport|date=21 May 2017|access-date=13 February 2018|archive-date=30 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330192200/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39926301|url-status=live}}</ref> and the [[2016–17 UEFA Champions League|2016–17 Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0250-0c5117c008df-de0901ea6dae-1000--majestic-real-madrid-win-champions-league-in-cardiff/|title=Majestic Real Madrid win Champions League in Cardiff|publisher=UEFA|date=3 June 2017|access-date=4 June 2017|archive-date=31 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331042605/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2017/matches/round=2000787/match=2019641/postmatch/report/index.html|url-status=live}}</ref> During the [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League|2017–18 Champions League]], Kovačić made six appearances as Madrid won their third consecutive—and 13th overall—Champions League title.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0245-0e98d7318379-716954065574-1000--madrid-beat-liverpool-to-complete-hat-trick/|title=Madrid beat Liverpool to complete hat-trick|publisher=UEFA|date=26 May 2018|access-date=28 May 2018|archive-date=27 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180527203029/http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2018/matches/round=2000885/match=2021711/postmatch/report/index.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Chelsea===
====2018–2020====
On 8 August 2018, Kovačić joined [[Premier League]] club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] on [[Loan (association football)|loan]] for the [[2018–19 Chelsea F.C. season|2018–19 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/08/official-announcement-mateo-kovacic|title=Official announcement: Mateo Kovacic|publisher=Real Madrid CF|date=8 August 2018|access-date=8 August 2018|archive-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229183644/https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/08/official-announcement-mateo-kovacic|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2018/8/8/courtois-and-kovacic-deals-agreed|title=Courtois and Kovacic deals agreed|publisher=Chelsea F.C.|date=8 August 2018|access-date=8 August 2018|archive-date=30 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230120047/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2018/8/8/courtois-and-kovacic-deals-agreed|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his debut in a 3–2 home win against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on 18 August, appearing as a second-half substitute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.givemesport.com/1374987-mateo-kovacics-individual-highlights-against-arsenal-have-now-emerged|title=Mateo Kovacic's individual highlights against Arsenal have now emerged|date=19 August 2018|work=GiveMeSport|access-date=19 August 2018|archive-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229183646/https://www.givemesport.com/1374987-mateo-kovacics-individual-highlights-against-arsenal-have-now-emerged|url-status=live}}</ref> On 29 May 2019, he started in the [[2019 UEFA Europa League final|2019 Europa League final]] in [[Baku]], playing until 78th minute when he was substituted off for [[Ross Barkley]], as Chelsea beat Arsenal 4–1.<ref>{{Cite news|date=29 May 2019|title=Chelsea beat Arsenal 4–1 to win Europa League final|website=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48368406|access-date=24 June 2020|archive-date=25 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210325045830/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48368406|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Murray|first=Scott|date=29 May 2019|title=Chelsea beat Arsenal 4–1 to win Europa League final – as it happened|work=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2019/may/29/chelsea-v-arsenal-europa-league-final-2019-live|access-date=24 June 2020|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=3 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803172923/https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2019/may/29/chelsea-v-arsenal-europa-league-final-2019-live|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:FC RB Salzburg versus Chelsea FC (Testspiel 31. Juli 2019) 13 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Kovačić playing for [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in 2019]]
On 1 July 2019, Kovačić completed a permanent transfer to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2019/07/official-announcement-kovacic|title=Official Announcement: Kovacic|publisher=Real Madrid CF|date=1 July 2019|access-date=1 July 2019|archive-date=12 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191012014016/https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2019/07/official-announcement-kovacic|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2019/07/01/mateo-kovacic-joins-chelsea-on-a-permanent-deal|title=Mateo Kovacic joins Chelsea on a permanent deal|publisher=Chelsea F.C.|date=1 July 2019|access-date=1 July 2019|archive-date=18 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191018181717/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2019/07/01/mateo-kovacic-joins-chelsea-on-a-permanent-deal|url-status=live}}</ref> After an underwhelming season under [[Maurizio Sarri]], Kovačić turned into one of the most important Chelsea players under new manager [[Frank Lampard]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Chambers|first=Reece|date=30 May 2020|title=Underrated Kovacic the key player in Chelsea's midfield|url=https://www.football.london/chelsea-fc/players/chelsea-mateo-kovacic-performance-lampard-18328458|access-date=24 June 2020|website=footballlondon|archive-date=4 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204020754/https://www.football.london/chelsea-fc/players/chelsea-mateo-kovacic-performance-lampard-18328458|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=A review of Mateo Kovacic's 2019/20 season at Chelsea |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2020/05/27/their-season-so-far--mateo-kovacic |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |access-date=24 June 2020 |quote=Under one of the all-time midfield greats, the Croatian has flourished. |archive-date=8 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200808191732/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2020/05/27/their-season-so-far--mateo-kovacic |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=26 April 2020|title=Mateo Kovačić Has Been Chelsea's Best Player This Season – Not Willian|url=https://www.90min.com/posts/6600435-mateo-kovacic-has-been-chelsea-s-best-player-this-season-not-willian|access-date=24 June 2020|website=90min.com|archive-date=3 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803213813/https://www.90min.com/posts/6600435-mateo-kovacic-has-been-chelsea-s-best-player-this-season-not-willian|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=15 December 2019|title=Is Mateo Kovacic Chelsea's most important player?|url=https://www.thechelseachronicle.com/club-news/is-mateo-kovacic-chelseas-most-important-player/|access-date=24 June 2020|website=The Chelsea Chronicle|quote=Some fans were unconvinced by the Croatian and did not support the signing. This opinion is likely to be very different now.|archive-date=3 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803181232/https://www.thechelseachronicle.com/club-news/is-mateo-kovacic-chelseas-most-important-player/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Forget Kante – Kovacic is the key to Chelsea's top-four hopes|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/forget-kante-kovacic-is-the-key-to-chelseas-top-four-hopes/1mipqgugixq91vugvp7thgv61|access-date=24 June 2020|website=Goal (website)|archive-date=18 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818105835/https://www.goal.com/en/news/forget-kante-kovacic-is-the-key-to-chelseas-top-four-hopes/1mipqgugixq91vugvp7thgv61|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Dixit|first=Vibudh|date=21 June 2020|title='Kovacic And Loftus-Cheek Are Chelsea's Best Midfielders' - Interview With Chelsea Journalist Simon Phillips|url=https://worldfootballindex.com/2020/06/kovacic-and-loftus-cheek-are-chelseas-best-midfielders-interview-with-chelsea-journalist-simon-phillips/|access-date=24 June 2020|website=World Football Index|archive-date=27 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127003904/https://worldfootballindex.com/2020/06/kovacic-and-loftus-cheek-are-chelseas-best-midfielders-interview-with-chelsea-journalist-simon-phillips/|url-status=live}}</ref> Kovačić scored his first goal for Chelsea on 27 November, in a 2–2 away draw against Valencia in the [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|2019–20 Champions League]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chowdhury |first1=Saj |title=Valencia 2–2 Chelsea |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50519896 |access-date=28 November 2019 |website=BBC Sport |date=27 November 2019 |archive-date=20 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020094625/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50519896 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 7 December, he scored his first Premier League goal in a 3–1 away loss to [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=McNulty |first1=Phil |title=Everton 3–1 Chelsea |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50611310 |access-date=7 December 2019 |website=BBC Sport |date=7 December 2019 |archive-date=24 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210524200249/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50611310 |url-status=live }}</ref> In the [[2020 FA Cup final]] on 1 August 2020, he was sent off for a challenge on [[Granit Xhaka]], as Chelsea lost 2–1 to Arsenal.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Anderson|first=Jamie|date=1 August 2020|title=Arsenal 2–1 Chelsea: Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang double guides Gunners to FA Cup final win|url=https://www.express.co.uk/sport/football/1316796/Arsenal-Chelsea-Live-FA-Cup-Final-Team-News-Line-Ups-Score-Latest|website=Daily Express|access-date=1 August 2020|archive-date=24 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124181502/https://www.express.co.uk/sport/football/1316796/Arsenal-Chelsea-Live-FA-Cup-Final-Team-News-Line-Ups-Score-Latest|url-status=live}}</ref> On 25 August, he was named the [[Chelsea F.C.#Player of the Year|Chelsea Player of the Year]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|date=25 August 2020|title=Chelsea Player of the Season 2019/20: Mateo Kovacic announced as winner|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2020/08/25/player-of-the-season--mateo-kovacic|publisher=Chelsea F.C.|access-date=25 August 2020|archive-date=23 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123162801/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2020/08/25/player-of-the-season--mateo-kovacic|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 23 September 2020, Kovačić marked his 100th appearance for the club against [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] in the third round of the [[2020–21 EFL Cup]] as Chelsea won 6–0 at home.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11713/12079578/chelsea-6-0-barnsley-kai-havertz-hits-hat-trick-as-blues-romp-into-round-four-of-carabao-cup|title=Chelsea 6–0 Barnsley: Kai Havertz hits hat-trick as Blues romp into round four of Carabao Cup|date=23 September 2020|website=Sky Sports|access-date=24 September 2020|archive-date=4 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210204072753/https://www.skysports.com/amp/football/news/11713/12079578/chelsea-6-0-barnsley-kai-havertz-hits-hat-trick-as-blues-romp-into-round-four-of-carabao-cup|url-status=live}}</ref> After a difficult start of the [[2020–21 Chelsea F.C. season|season]], Kovačić regained form from the previous season following the appointment of new manager [[Thomas Tuchel]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Phillips|first=Simon|date=5 February 2021|title=Mateo Kovacic explains exactly how Thomas Tuchel is telling them to play|url=https://www.chelsea-news.co/2021/02/mateo-kovacic-explains-exactly-thomas-tuchel-telling-play/|access-date=5 February 2021|website=Chelsea News|archive-date=21 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210221150213/https://www.chelsea-news.co/2021/02/mateo-kovacic-explains-exactly-thomas-tuchel-telling-play/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Johnson |first=Simon |date=5 February 2021 |title=Kovacic has a head start in winning Tuchel's backing. He'll be hard to dislodge |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/2369059/2021/02/05/kovacic-has-a-head-start-in-winning-tuchels-backing-hell-be-hard-to-dislodge/ |access-date=2025-04-15 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Topić|first=Mihovil|date=2 March 2021|title=Kovačić je spreman za iskorak|url=https://telesport.telegram.hr/analize/kovacic-je-spreman-za-iskorak/|access-date=4 March 2021|website=Telesport|language=hr|archive-date=7 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307143314/https://telesport.telegram.hr/analize/kovacic-je-spreman-za-iskorak/|url-status=live}}</ref> Ahead of the second leg of the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Quarter-finals|2020–21 Champions League quarter-finals]] against Porto, Kovačić sustained a tendon injury and was forced to miss the semi-final tie against his former club Real Madrid, which Chelsea won 3–1 on aggregate.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Rathborn|first=Jack|date=23 April 2021|title=Thomas Tuchel gives Mateo Kovacic injury update with Croatian ruled out against Madrid|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/chelsea-mateo-kovacic-injury-news-b1836474.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220512/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/chelsea-mateo-kovacic-injury-news-b1836474.html |archive-date=12 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|access-date=25 April 2021|website=The Independent}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Starešinčić |first=Danijel |date=24 April 2021 |title=Hrvatski veznjak Mateo Kovačić definitivno prekrižen; trener Chelsea Thomas Tuchel objasnio kako to jednostavno nije moguće |url=https://www.tportal.hr/sport/clanak/hrvatski-veznjak-mateo-kovacic-definitivno-prekrizen-trener-chelsea-thomas-tuchel-objasnio-kako-to-jednostavno-nije-moguce-foto-20210424 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210428030152/https://www.tportal.hr/sport/clanak/hrvatski-veznjak-mateo-kovacic-definitivno-prekrizen-trener-chelsea-thomas-tuchel-objasnio-kako-to-jednostavno-nije-moguce-foto-20210424 |archive-date=28 April 2021 |access-date=25 April 2021 |website=Tportal.hr |language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Rathborn|first=Jack|date=4 May 2021|title=Mateo Kovacic ruled out against Real Madrid through injury|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/chelsea-real-madrid-team-news-kovacic-b1841876.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220512/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/chelsea-real-madrid-team-news-kovacic-b1841876.html |archive-date=12 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|access-date=5 May 2021|website=The Independent}}</ref> Despite previously winning three Champions Leagues, on 29 May 2021, Kovačić played in a [[2021 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]] for the first time in his career, coming on for [[Mason Mount]] in the 80th minute, as Chelsea beat [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] 1–0.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Šola |first1=Robert |last2=Mršnik |first2=Patrik |date=29 May 2021 |title=VIDEO: Čudesni Chelsea prvak Europe, Kovačić odigrao najvažnije minute u životu, Guardiola na koljenima! |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/liga-prvaka/video-cudesni-chelsea-prvak-europe-kovacic-odigrao-najvaznije-minute-u-zivotu-guardiola-na-koljenima-15076946 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210602213325/https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/liga-prvaka/video-cudesni-chelsea-prvak-europe-kovacic-odigrao-najvaznije-minute-u-zivotu-guardiola-na-koljenima-15076946 |archive-date=2 June 2021 |access-date=29 May 2021 |website=Sportske novosti |language=hr-hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=29 May 2021 |title=Kovačić je napokon uspio: Dostigao je Modrićev rekord i nastavio čudesni hrvatski niz |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/kovacic-je-napokon-zaigrao-u-finalu-lige-prvaka-dostigao-je-modricev-rekord-i-nastavio-cudesni-hrvatski-niz---653805.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603041817/https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/kovacic-je-napokon-zaigrao-u-finalu-lige-prvaka-dostigao-je-modricev-rekord-i-nastavio-cudesni-hrvatski-niz---653805.html |archive-date=3 June 2021 |access-date=29 May 2021 |website=Gol.hr |language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0269-12650cedca55-37515f69768e-1000--report-chelsea-claim-second-title/|title=Man. City 0–1 Chelsea: Havertz gives Blues second Champions League triumph|publisher=UEFA|date=29 May 2021|accessdate=29 May 2021|archive-date=3 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603073706/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0269-12650cedca55-37515f69768e-1000--report-chelsea-claim-second-title/|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2021–2023====
On 11 September 2021, Kovačić provided [[Romelu Lukaku]] with an assist and scored in a 3–0 victory over [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tolić |first=Josip |date=11 September 2021 |title=VIDEO Kovina partija godine! Čudesna asistencija za Lukakua pa prvi gol za Chelsea od 2019. |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/video-kovina-partija-godine-cudesna-asistencija-za-lukakua-pa-prvi-gol-za-chelsea-od-2019-783724 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210911185602/https://www.24sata.hr/sport/video-kovina-partija-godine-cudesna-asistencija-za-lukakua-pa-prvi-gol-za-chelsea-od-2019-783724 |archive-date=11 September 2021 |access-date=11 September 2021 |website=24sata |language=hr}}</ref> In late October, Kovačić suffered an injury in training and then tested positive for [[COVID-19]] in early December.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Steinberg |first=Jacob |date=7 December 2021 |title=Mateo Kovacic tests positive for Covid in 'huge setback' for Chelsea's Tuchel |language=en-GB |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/dec/07/mateo-kovacic-tests-positive-for-covid-in-huge-setback-for-chelseas-tuchel |access-date=2023-06-23 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=23 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230623153307/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/dec/07/mateo-kovacic-tests-positive-for-covid-in-huge-setback-for-chelseas-tuchel |url-status=live }}</ref> He returned to the team on 19 December, in a 0–0 draw with [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=23 December 2021|title='The plan': Tuchel shares the real reason why he took Kovacic off at half-time vs Brentford|url=https://www.thechelseachronicle.com/efl-cup/the-plan-tuchel-shares-the-real-reason-why-he-took-kovacic-off-at-half-time-vs-brentford/|access-date=2 January 2022|website=The Chelsea Chronicle|archive-date=2 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220102183951/https://www.thechelseachronicle.com/efl-cup/the-plan-tuchel-shares-the-real-reason-why-he-took-kovacic-off-at-half-time-vs-brentford/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 2 January 2022, he initiated a comeback in a 2–2 home draw with [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], in which he scored Chelsea's first goal while they were two goals down.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Lawless|first=Josh|date=2 January 2022|title=Mateo Kovacic Scores Outrageous Volley Against Liverpool|url=https://www.sportbible.com/football/mateo-kovacic-scores-absolutely-outrageous-volley-against-liverpool-20220102|url-status=live|access-date=2 January 2022|website=Sport Bible|archive-date=2 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220102173719/https://www.sportbible.com/football/mateo-kovacic-scores-absolutely-outrageous-volley-against-liverpool-20220102}}</ref> He later won the [[Premier League Goal of the Month]] and the [[2021–22 Chelsea F.C. season#Awards|Chelsea Goal of the Year]] for this goal.<ref>{{Cite web|date=4 February 2022|title=Kovacic Volley Voted January 2022 Budweiser Goal of the Month|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/2470108|publisher=Premier League|access-date=6 March 2022|archive-date=19 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221019095601/https://www.premierleague.com/news/2470108|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=1 June 2022 |title=Kovacic wins Chelsea Goal of the Season |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2022/06/01/kovacic-wins-chelsea-goal-of-the-season |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |access-date=2 June 2022 |archive-date=1 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220601123359/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2022/06/01/kovacic-wins-chelsea-goal-of-the-season |url-status=live }}</ref> Six days later, on 8 January, Kovačić captained Chelsea for the first time in a 5–1 victory over [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]] in the [[2021–22 FA Cup|FA Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=8 January 2022|title=Chelsea line up vs Chesterfield {{!}} Official Site|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2022/01/08/chelsea-line-up-vs-chesterfield|publisher=Chelsea F.C.|access-date=9 January 2022|archive-date=8 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108184405/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2022/01/08/chelsea-line-up-vs-chesterfield|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=8 January 2022|title='Hitting his best form': Some Chelsea fans loved their senior player's display in 5–1 FA Cup win|url=https://www.thechelseachronicle.com/fan-views/hitting-his-best-form-some-chelsea-fans-loved-their-senior-players-display-in-5-1-fa-cup-win/|access-date=9 January 2022|website=The Chelsea Chronicle|archive-date=9 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220109040419/https://www.thechelseachronicle.com/fan-views/hitting-his-best-form-some-chelsea-fans-loved-their-senior-players-display-in-5-1-fa-cup-win/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 7 March 2023, Kovačić captained Chelsea in the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|2022–23 Champions League round of 16]], leading them to a 2–0 victory over [[Borussia Dortmund]] and into the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Quarter-finals|quarter-finals]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/uzivo-liga-prvaka-chelsea-borussia-dortmund---770027.html |date=7 March 2023 |access-date=8 March 2023 |language=hr |website=[[Gol.hr]] |title=Chelsea s kapetanom Kovačićem nadoknadio minus i prošao u četvrtfinale Lige prvaka |archive-date=7 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230307231445/https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/uzivo-liga-prvaka-chelsea-borussia-dortmund---770027.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/englezi-hvale-matea-kovacica-svi-izdvajaju-kako-je-unistio-judea-bellinghama---770076.html |access-date=8 March 2022 |date=8 March 2022 |language=hr |website=[[Gol.hr]] |title=VIDEO Kovačić oduševio Engleze, a svi izdvajaju jedan detalj: Izigrao je Modrićeva nasljednika |archive-date=8 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230308084437/https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/englezi-hvale-matea-kovacica-svi-izdvajaju-kako-je-unistio-judea-bellinghama---770076.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Four days later, on 11 March, Kovačić captained Chelsea again and scored the third goal in a 3–1 victory over [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] in the [[2022–23 Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/12828898/leicester-1-3-chelsea-ben-chilwell-kai-havertz-and-mateo-kovacic-score-to-further-ease-pressure-on-graham-potter |title=Leicester 1–3 Chelsea: Ben Chilwell, Kai Havertz and Mateo Kovacic score to further ease pressure on Graham Potter |date=11 March 2023 |access-date=12 March 2023 |website=Sky Sports |first=David |last=Richardson |archive-date=11 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230311213455/http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/12828898/leicester-1-3-chelsea-ben-chilwell-kai-havertz-and-mateo-kovacic-score-to-further-ease-pressure-on-graham-potter |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=12 March 2023 |title=Kovačić zaludio Engleze: Chelsea je objavio i njegovu pjesmu, a trener je u transu |trans-title=Kovačić has dazzled the English: Chelsea even released his song, and the coach is in a trance. |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/mateo-kovacic-zaludio-engleze---770768.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230312101110/https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/mateo-kovacic-zaludio-engleze---770768.html |archive-date=12 March 2023 |access-date=12 March 2023 |website=[[Gol.hr]] |language=hr}}</ref>

===Manchester City===
[[File:Yokohama F. Marinos - Manchester City (3-5) - 53075077396 (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|Kovačić (right) in a friendly game for Manchester City against [[Yokohama F. Marinos]] in 2023]]
On 27 June 2023, fellow Premier League club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] announced the signing of Kovačić on a four-year deal.<ref>{{Cite news |last=City |first=Man |date=27 June 2023 |title=City complete Kovacic signing |pages=1 |work=Man City |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/mateo-kovacic-joins-manchester-city-63823479 |url-status=bot: unknown |access-date=27 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230627170939/https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/mateo-kovacic-joins-manchester-city-63823479 |archive-date=27 June 2023 }}</ref> He became the third Croatian to sign for the club, after [[Vedran Ćorluka]] and [[Ante Palaversa]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tolić |first1=Josip |last2=Miličić |first2=Dubravko |date=27 June 2023 |title=Službeno: Mateo Kovačić novi je nogometaš Manchester Cityja! Ovo su svi detalji velikog posla |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/sluzbeno-mateo-kovacic-novi-je-nogometas-manchester-cityja-ovo-su-svi-detalji-velikog-posla-918982 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230628081643/https://www.24sata.hr/sport/sluzbeno-mateo-kovacic-novi-je-nogometas-manchester-cityja-ovo-su-svi-detalji-velikog-posla-918982 |archive-date=28 June 2023 |access-date=2023-06-28 |website=[[24sata (Croatia)|24sata]] |language=hr}}</ref> On 6 August, he made his competitive debut for the club against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the [[2023 FA Community Shield|FA Community Shield]], which City lost 4–1 on penalties after a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{Cite web |date=6 August 2023 |title=Arsenal 1–1 Man City (4–1 on pens) |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/arsenal-vs-manchester-city/report/482389 |language=en}}</ref> Kovačić won his first trophy at City on 16 August, as the Mancunian side defeated [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] 5–4 on penalties following a 1–1 draw in the [[2023 UEFA Super Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefasupercup/news/0284-18c07e15b0ff-af3118a0e297-1000/ |title=Manchester City 1–1 Sevilla (Man City win 5–4 on penalties): Shoot-out drama as Man City win UEFA Super Cup |publisher=[[UEFA]] |date=16 August 2023 |access-date=16 August 2023}}</ref> with Kovačić scoring in the shootout. On 19 December 2023, Kovačić scored his first goal for Manchester City in a 3–0 [[2023 FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Cup]] semi-final win against [[Urawa Red Diamonds]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Manchester City 3-0 Urawa Red Diamonds (Dec 19, 2023) Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/687850 |access-date=2023-12-19 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

On 19 August 2024, in Manchester City's opening match of the [[2024–25 Premier League]] season, Kovačić scored his second league goal for Manchester City as they beat his former club Chelsea 2–0 at Stamford Bridge.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c4gdp5xexn7t#Report|title=Chelsea 0–2 Manchester City|access-date=19 August 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth career===
Kovačić appeared for the Croatia national team at various youth levels, debuting in May 2008 in an under-14 friendly match against Slovakia.<ref name="hns">{{cite web |url=http://www.hns-cff.hr/?ln=hr&w=statistike&repka=U&id=156397 |title=Statistike&nbsp;— Nastupi: Mateo Kovačić |publisher=Croatian Football Federation |language=hr |access-date=20 November 2010 |archive-date=23 October 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023113816/http://www.hns-cff.hr/?ln=hr |url-status=live }}</ref> Since 2011, he was a regular member of the [[Croatia national under-19 football team|under-19]] and [[Croatia national under-21 football team|under-21 teams]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hns.team/en/players/156397/mateo-kovacic/|title=Mateo Kovačić|publisher=[[Croatian Football Federation]]|access-date=12 October 2025}}</ref>

===Senior career===
====2012–2018====
[[File:ISL-HRV (9) (cropped) Mateo Kovačić.jpg|thumb|upright|Kovačić playing for Croatia at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]
In August 2012, Kovačić received his first competitive call-up for the [[Croatia national football team|Croatian senior team]] match against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]], but did not play because of injury.<ref>{{cite news |date=30 July 2012 |title=Štimac pozvao Kovačića |url=http://sportske.jutarnji.hr/igor-stimac-za-svicarsku-pozvao-malocu--vukusica--kovacica--sammir-jos-uvijek-na-cekanju/1044377/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120801212450/http://sportske.jutarnji.hr/igor-stimac-za-svicarsku-pozvao-malocu--vukusica--kovacica--sammir-jos-uvijek-na-cekanju/1044377 |archive-date=1 August 2012 |access-date=31 January 2013 |language=hr}}</ref> Subsequently, he received a call up for [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches in March 2013. He made his senior debut in a qualification match against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] on 22 March, playing as a central midfielder alongside Luka Modrić, instead of a regular team starter, [[Ognjen Vukojević]].<ref>{{cite web |date=22 March 2013 |title=Štimac: "Odluku o Kovačiću 'prelomio' sam sinoć, odigrao je za desetku" |url=http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/458465/nogomet-reprezentacija/stimac-odluku-o-kovacicu-prelomio-sam-sinoc-odigrao-je-za-desetku/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130325000035/http://www.hrsport.net/vijesti/458465/nogomet-reprezentacija/stimac-odluku-o-kovacicu-prelomio-sam-sinoc-odigrao-je-za-desetku/ |archive-date=25 March 2013 |access-date=23 March 2013 |publisher=Sportnet |language=hr}}</ref> Four days later, he played against [[Wales national football team|Wales]] at the [[Liberty Stadium]], coming on as a second-half substitute in a 1–2 win. His third match of the campaign came in June, when Croatia faced [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] in Zagreb and suffered a frustrating defeat as they were unable to score despite a string of good chances. By the end of the qualifiers, Kovačić made two more competitive appearances for Croatia, as Croatia scraped into the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification&nbsp;– UEFA second round|FIFA World Cup play-offs]] having taken only one point from their last four qualifiers. Although he did not participate in the scoreless first leg of the play-off against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] in [[Reykjavík]], Kovačić started the second leg between the two teams in Zagreb, making an assist for the team's second goal as they reached the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] with a 2–0 win on aggregate.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ten-man Croatia reached the 2014 World Cup finals |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/24907602 |date=19 November 2013 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=31 January 2014 |archive-date=17 January 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140117094027/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/24907602 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 2 June 2014, Kovačić was named as a member of Croatia's [[2014 FIFA World Cup squads#Croatia|World Cup squad]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/croatia/10810185/Croatia-World-Cup-2014-squad.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220112/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/croatia/10810185/Croatia-World-Cup-2014-squad.html |archive-date=12 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Croatia World Cup 2014 squad |date=2 June 2014 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=19 June 2014}}{{cbignore}}</ref> He was in Croatia's starting team for the opening game of the tournament, a 3–1 defeat to World Cup hosts [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] at the [[Arena Corinthians]], São Paulo, where he played for his team for 60 minutes before being substituted.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/25285029 |title=Brazil 3–1 Croatia |date=12 June 2014 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=20 June 2014 |archive-date=23 January 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160123011908/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/25285029 |url-status=live }}</ref> He went to play all the remaining games in the group stage, as Croatia was eliminated in the group stage. On 7 June 2015, he scored his first international goal in a 4–0 victory over [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]], coming in his 20th appearance for the team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.croatiaweek.com/croatia-4-0-gibraltar-mission-accomplished-kovac|title=Croatia 4–0 Gibraltar: 'Mission Accomplished' – Kovač|date=8 June 2015|work=Croatia Week|access-date=23 June 2018|archive-date=23 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180623141519/https://www.croatiaweek.com/croatia-4-0-gibraltar-mission-accomplished-kovac/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 4 June 2018, Kovačić was selected in [[Zlatko Dalić]]'s [[2018 FIFA World Cup squads#Croatia|23-man squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportsnet.ca/soccer/modric-rakitic-headline-croatias-world-cup-squad|title=Modric, Rakitic headline Croatia's World Cup squad|publisher=Sportsnet|access-date=23 June 2018|archive-date=13 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613055458/https://www.sportsnet.ca/soccer/modric-rakitic-headline-croatias-world-cup-squad/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 June, Kovačić provided an assist to his teammate [[Ivan Rakitić]] as he scored Croatia's third goal in a 3–0 win over [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in their second [[2018 FIFA World Cup Group D|group stage]] match of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/1249922/Live/International-FIFA-World-Cup-2018-Argentina-Croatia|title=Argentina 0–3 Croatia – FIFA World Cup 2018 Live|publisher=Whoscored.com|access-date=23 June 2018|archive-date=5 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705024419/https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/1249922/Live/International-FIFA-World-Cup-2018-Argentina-Croatia|url-status=live}}</ref> Croatia was beaten 4–2 by [[France national football team|France]] in [[2018 FIFA World Cup final|the final]] on 15 July.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44754965 |title=France 4–2 Croatia |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=15 July 2018 |access-date=29 April 2023 |archive-date=25 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325011256/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44754965 |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2018–present====
Kovačić appeared in Croatia's [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League A]] matches against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] away and [[England national football team|England]] home, that ended up as 6–0 defeat and a goalless draw, respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hall|first=Pete|date=12 September 2018|title=Spain 6–0 Croatia: Marco Asensio stars in Nations League as visitors suffer worst-ever defeat|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/spain-vs-croatia/report/399738|access-date=24 June 2020|website=Sky Sports|archive-date=26 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626184203/https://www.skysports.com/football/spain-vs-croatia/report/399738|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=11 September 2018|title=Nations League: Superb Spain put six past Croatia|website=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45489521|access-date=24 June 2020|archive-date=5 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805024711/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45489521|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=McNulty|first=Phil|date=12 October 2018|title=Croatia 0–0 England: England hit woodwork twice in goalless draw|website=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45755081|access-date=24 June 2020|archive-date=29 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329130453/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45755081|url-status=live}}</ref> He featured throughout Croatia's successful [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying|Euro 2020 qualifying]] campaign, as they finished top of the [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying Group E|group]]. In a 2–1 win over Wales in [[Osijek]] on 8 June 2019, he scored what would have been a goal for 2–0, however it was disallowed as [[Andrej Kramarić]] was in an offside position.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Buškulić |first=Ante |date=8 June 2019 |title=Kramarić zeznuo Kovačića u pobjedi koja je izborena srcem |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/kramaric-zeznuo-kovacica-u-pobjedi-koja-je-izborena-srcem-633644 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200627204216/https://www.24sata.hr/sport/kramaric-zeznuo-kovacica-u-pobjedi-koja-je-izborena-srcem-633644 |archive-date=27 June 2020 |access-date=24 June 2020 |website=24sata |language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=8 June 2019 |title=Hrvatska pobijedila Wales i osvojila važne bodove u borbi za Euro 2020.! |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/live-hrvatska-wales-sve-o-prijenosu-uzivo-na-novoj-tv-i-gol-hr-u---562581.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626184203/https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/live-hrvatska-wales-sve-o-prijenosu-uzivo-na-novoj-tv-i-gol-hr-u---562581.html |archive-date=26 June 2020 |access-date=24 June 2020 |website=Gol.hr |language=hr}}</ref> In a return leg on 13 October, in the build-up to Wales' goal, Kovačić was controversially injured by [[Ben Davies (footballer, born 1993)|Ben Davies]] as the match ended up as a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Euro 2020 qualifiers: Wales held by group leaders Croatia – reaction|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/live/football/49377391?page=6|access-date=24 June 2020|website=BBC Sport|date=13 October 2019 |archive-date=27 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200627051655/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/live/football/49377391/page/6|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=M. J. |title=Velški mediji: Talisman Bale razočarao Hrvate, Kovačić nije dočekao prekršaj |url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2123660 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230629091715/https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/velski-mediji-talisman-bale-razocarao-hrvate-kovacic-nije-docekao-prekrsaj/2123660.aspx |archive-date=29 June 2023 |access-date=24 June 2020 |website=Index.hr |language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=13 October 2019|title=DRUŠTVENE MREŽE GORE NAKON SUDAČKE KONTROVERZE: 'Bio je to prekršaj, Hrvatska je pokradena'|url=https://net.hr/sport/nogomet/drustvene-mreze-gore-nakon-sudacke-kontroverze-godine-bio-je-to-prekrsaj-hrvatska-je-pokradena/|access-date=24 June 2020|website=Net.hr|language=hr|archive-date=26 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626170942/https://net.hr/sport/nogomet/drustvene-mreze-gore-nakon-sudacke-kontroverze-godine-bio-je-to-prekrsaj-hrvatska-je-pokradena/|url-status=live}}</ref>

During Croatia's [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League A|2020–21 Nations League A]] campaign, Kovačić was heavily criticised for his inefficiency in the national team,<ref>{{Cite web|date=6 September 2020|title=Ćiro Blažević: Kovačić je promašaj, više mu nije mjesto u reprezentaciji|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2210702|access-date=18 November 2020|website=Index.hr|language=hr|archive-date=29 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230629091715/https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/ciro-blazevic-dalic-je-slijep-ne-vidi-koliko-je-kovacic-los/2210702.aspx|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Mati |first=Stjepan |date=8 September 2020 |title=Treneri i igrači o misteriju Matea Kovačića: Samo ga šaltaju, on ne zna što igra |url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2211087 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230629091715/https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/do-kad-cemo-cekati-matea-kovacica/2211087.aspx |archive-date=29 June 2023 |access-date=18 November 2020 |website=Index.hr |language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=18 November 2020|title=Dalić: Mi napadamo Kovačića, mi samo pljujemo. Je li to normalno?|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2231331|website=Index.hr|language=hr|access-date=18 November 2020|archive-date=29 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230629091716/https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/dalic-mi-napadamo-kovacica-mi-samo-pljujemo-je-li-to-normalno/2231331.aspx|url-status=live}}</ref> especially after making an error that led to [[Dejan Kulusevski|Dejan Kuluševski]]'s opening goal in Croatia's crucial match against [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] on 14 November 2020, that eventually finished as a 2–1 defeat.<ref>{{Cite web|date=14 November 2020|title=Bjelica: Hrvatska šalje krivu poruku, a najveća greška je Kovačić|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2230452|access-date=18 November 2020|website=Index.hr|language=hr|archive-date=29 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230629091716/https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/bjelica-hrvatska-salje-krivu-poruku-a-najveca-greska-je-kovacic/2230452.aspx|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Škrlec|first=Silvijo|date=15 November 2020|title=Miroslav Ćiro Blažević ukazao na slabosti u igri Matea Kovačića, ali ovog puta nije prozvao samo njega: Oni nemaju mjesta u ovoj momčadi|url=https://www.tportal.hr/sport/clanak/miroslav-ciro-blazevic-ukazao-na-slabosti-u-igri-matea-kovacica-ali-ovog-puta-nije-prozvao-samo-njega-oni-nemaju-mjesta-u-ovoj-momcadi-foto-20201114|access-date=18 November 2020|website=Tportal.hr|language=hr|archive-date=15 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201115145754/https://www.tportal.hr/sport/clanak/miroslav-ciro-blazevic-ukazao-na-slabosti-u-igri-matea-kovacica-ali-ovog-puta-nije-prozvao-samo-njega-oni-nemaju-mjesta-u-ovoj-momcadi-foto-20201114|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Galić|first=Mato|date=14 November 2020|title=Mateo, pa daj se konačno trgni!|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/mateo-pa-daj-se-konacno-trgni-728173|access-date=18 November 2020|website=24sata|language=hr|archive-date=7 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211207222924/https://www.24sata.hr/sport/mateo-pa-daj-se-konacno-trgni-728173|url-status=live}}</ref> However, three days later, he scored two goals in a 3–2 defeat to [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]], which eventually saved Croatia from relegation to the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League B|2022–23 Nations League B]] as they achieved better goal difference than Sweden.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Krušelj|first=Dražen|date=18 November 2020|title=Zaslužili smo ostanak! Naš gard bio je jasan odmah nakon što je Lovren zagalamio na Pašalića...|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/zasluzili-smo-ostanak-nas-gard-bio-je-jasan-odmah-nakon-sto-je-lovren-zagalamio-na-pasalica-15031949|access-date=18 November 2020|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr|archive-date=1 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201201110007/https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/zasluzili-smo-ostanak-nas-gard-bio-je-jasan-odmah-nakon-sto-je-lovren-zagalamio-na-pasalica-15031949|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Hina|date=17 November 2020|title=Drama za Hrvate: Portugal slavio u Splitu, ali Vatreni ostaju u elitnom razredu|url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/uzivo-od-20-45-hrvatska-odlucuje-o-svojoj-sudbini-u-elitnom-razredu-lige-nacija-1446869|access-date=18 November 2020|website=Večernji list|language=hr|archive-date=16 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116212447/https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/uzivo-od-20-45-hrvatska-odlucuje-o-svojoj-sudbini-u-elitnom-razredu-lige-nacija-1446869|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Hrnčić|first=Fabijan|date=18 November 2020|title=Luka čestitao Kovi: Bravo, brate|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/luka-cestitao-kovi-bravo-brate-728973|access-date=19 November 2020|website=24sata|language=hr|archive-date=17 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210117135334/https://www.24sata.hr/amp/sport/luka-cestitao-kovi-bravo-brate-728973|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 17 May 2021, Kovačić was selected in Dalić's [[UEFA Euro 2020 squads#Croatia|26-man squad]] for [[UEFA Euro 2020]]<ref>{{Cite web|date=17 May 2021|title=Dalić: "Ovo je najbolje što Hrvatska ima"|url=https://hns-cff.hr/news/22677/dalic-ovo-je-najbolje-sto-hrvatska-ima/|access-date=25 June 2021|publisher=Croatian Football Federation|language=hr|archive-date=23 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210623022746/https://hns-cff.hr/news/22677/dalic-ovo-je-najbolje-sto-hrvatska-ima/|url-status=live}}</ref> and started all three [[UEFA Euro 2020 Group D|group stage]] matches.{{citation needed|date=April 2023}} In contrast to Croatia's Nations League campaign, his performances earned him widespread praise in the country as Croatia finished as the group runners-up and progressed to the [[UEFA Euro 2020 knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Fulurija|first=Emir|date=23 June 2021|title='Ne može s Lukom i Brozom', godinama ga kritiziraju, a brojke su jasne – on je najbolji Vatreni na EURU!|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/ne-moze-s-lukom-i-brozom-godinama-ga-kritiziraju-a-brojke-su-jasne-on-je-najbolji-vatreni-na-euru-15083015|access-date=25 June 2021|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr|archive-date=25 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210625071737/https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/ne-moze-s-lukom-i-brozom-godinama-ga-kritiziraju-a-brojke-su-jasne-on-je-najbolji-vatreni-na-euru-15083015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Pletikosa|first=Stipe|author-link=Stipe Pletikosa|date=24 June 2021|title='Bravo Modriću, ali drugi igrač je bio najbolji! U 29. minuti 'zamrzavam' sliku, brojim naše igrače...'|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/bravo-modricu-ali-drugi-igrac-je-bio-najbolji-u-29-minuti-zamrzavam-sliku-brojim-nase-igrace-15083250|access-date=25 June 2021|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr|archive-date=24 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624235842/https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/bravo-modricu-ali-drugi-igrac-je-bio-najbolji-u-29-minuti-zamrzavam-sliku-brojim-nase-igrace-15083250|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Sušec|first=Siniša|date=24 June 2021|title='Naš najbolje ocijenjeni igrač? On nije lošiji od De Bruynea, šteta što nije završio kod Guardiole...'|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/nas-najbolje-ocijenjeni-igrac-on-nije-losiji-od-de-bruynea-steta-sto-nije-zavrsio-kod-guardiole-15083299|access-date=25 June 2021|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr|archive-date=25 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210625023817/https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/nas-najbolje-ocijenjeni-igrac-on-nije-losiji-od-de-bruynea-steta-sto-nije-zavrsio-kod-guardiole-15083299|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Juranović|first=Tomislav|date=25 June 2021|title=Modrić, Kovačić i Perišić su hrvatske perjanice prvog dijela turnira, a dvojica su igrača najveći dužnici|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/modric-kovacic-i-perisic-su-hrvatske-perjanice-prvog-dijela-turnira-a-dvojica-su-igraca-najveci-duznici-15083411|access-date=25 June 2021|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr|archive-date=25 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210625071903/https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/modric-kovacic-i-perisic-su-hrvatske-perjanice-prvog-dijela-turnira-a-dvojica-su-igraca-najveci-duznici-15083411|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Karin|first=Vice|date=1 July 2021|title=Pred Kovačićem je najteža zadaća u povijesti reprezentacije|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2287128|access-date=1 July 2021|website=Index.hr|language=hr|archive-date=29 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230629091716/https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/pred-kovacicem-je-najteza-zadaca-u-povijesti-reprezentacije/2287128.aspx|url-status=live}}</ref> On 3 June 2022, in a 3–0 defeat to [[Austria national football team|Austria]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League A|2022–23 Nations League A]], Kovačić captained Croatia for the first time.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Đukarić |first=Gradimir |date=3 June 2022 |title=Debakl Vatrenih i prosipanje ugleda! Hrvatska izgubila 3:0 protiv Austrije, a stiže Francuska |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/debakl-vatrenih-i-prosipanje-ugleda-hrvatska-izgubila-3-0-protiv-austrije-a-stize-francuska-15206099 |access-date=4 June 2022 |website=Sportske novosti |language=hr-hr |archive-date=3 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220603211015/https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/debakl-vatrenih-i-prosipanje-ugleda-hrvatska-izgubila-3-0-protiv-austrije-a-stize-francuska-15206099 |url-status=live }}</ref> At the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], Kovačić received further praise for his performances as Croatia finished in [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Third place play-off|third place]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.index.hr/mobile/sport/clanak/jedan-igrac-zasluzuje-posebnu-pocast-uz-livakovica-i-gvardiola-najbolji-na-spu/2422067.aspx |title="Jedan igrač zaslužuje posebnu počast. Uz Livakovića i Gvardiola najbolji na SP-u" |website=Index.hr |date=18 December 2022 |access-date=19 December 2022 |language=hr |archive-date=29 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230629092722/https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/jedan-igrac-zasluzuje-posebnu-pocast-uz-livakovica-i-gvardiola-najbolji-na-spu/2422067.aspx |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.index.hr/mobile/sport/clanak/cesto-smo-zbog-njega-bili-tuzni-sad-nas-je-uvjerio-da-ce-biti-vodja-kad-luka-ode/2421934.aspx |title=Često smo zbog njega bili tužni, sad nas je uvjerio da će biti vođa kad Luka ode |date=18 December 2022 |access-date=19 December 2022 |language=hr |website=Index.hr |first=Krunoslav |last=Rendulić |author-link=Krunoslav Rendulić |archive-date=29 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230629092718/https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/cesto-smo-zbog-njega-bili-tuzni-sad-nas-je-uvjerio-da-ce-biti-vodja-kad-luka-ode/2421934.aspx |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 20 May 2024, he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=20 May 2024 |title=Croatia head coach Dalić presents preliminary EURO 2024 squad |url=https://hns.team/en/news/27852/croatia-head-coach-dalic-presents-preliminary-euro-2024-squad/ |publisher=[[Croatian Football Federation]] |access-date=30 May 2024}}</ref> A few weeks later, on 3 June, he earned his 100th international cap in a 3–0 friendly match win against [[North Macedonia national football team|North Macedonia]] prior to the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/mateo-kovacic-daj-boze-da-osvojimo-zlato-u-njemackoj-986386 |title=Mateo Kovačić kapetan u 100. nastupu: I u Njemačkoj ću ići u noćne šetnje s Modrićem |publisher=24sata.hr |language=hr |date=3 June 2024 }}</ref>

==Player profile==
===Style of play===
Kovačić started off as an [[attacking midfielder]] at [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]], but he transformed his game at [[Inter Milan|Inter]] where he was deployed out wide and also as a central midfielder, functioning as a deep-lying playmaker, while being coached by [[Andrea Stramaccioni]].<ref name="Mehrotra">{{cite web |last=Mehrotra |first=Aakriti |title=Mateo Kovacic: Scout Report&nbsp;— Inter's creative midfield talent |url=http://outsideoftheboot.com/2014/01/23/mateo-kovacic-scout-report/ |work=Outside of the Boot |access-date=1 February 2014 |date=22 January 2014 |archive-date=21 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200921061227/http://outsideoftheboot.com/2014/01/23/mateo-kovacic-scout-report/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> One of his trademarks is dropping deep to receive the ball and then driving forward, often performing his slalom runs.<ref name="Mehrotra" /> Under [[Walter Mazzarri]], Kovačić was often used in a more advanced position. Former manager [[Giovanni Trapattoni]] once claimed that Kovačić knows how to reach the ball from deep and drive up the pitch like a "raging bull".<ref name="MM">{{cite web |last=Higgins |first=Timm |title=Could Mateo Kovacic Be The Heir To Luka Modric's Crown? |url=http://www.managingmadrid.com/2017/2/10/14557684/could-mateo-kovacic-be-the-heir-to-luka-modrics-crown |work=Managing Madrid |access-date=12 February 2017 |date=10 February 2017 |archive-date=13 February 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170213002747/http://www.managingmadrid.com/2017/2/10/14557684/could-mateo-kovacic-be-the-heir-to-luka-modrics-crown |url-status=live }}</ref> Proven by his [[Passing (association football)|pass]] completion percentages, Kovačić is known for distributing the ball up the pitch.<ref name="MM" />

Kovačić's style of play is characterised by exceptional ball retention and counter-pressing abilities.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |title=Mateo Kovacic: Premier League Player Watch |url=https://www.coachesvoice.com/cv/mateo-kovacic-chelsea-real-madrid/ |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=The Coaches' Voice |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite web |last=Ellis |first=Charlie |date=19 July 2023 |title=Why Mateo Kovačić is perfect for Manchester City |url=https://themastermindsite.com/2023/07/19/why-mateo-kovacic-is-perfect-for-manchester-city/ |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=TheMastermindSite |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":5">{{Cite web |last=alimangi7 |date=4 July 2023 |title=Transfer Spotlight: Man City's Mateo Kovacic |url=https://www.nevermanagealone.com/2023/7/4/23781738/nma-epl-summer-transfer-spotlight-man-city-mateo-kovacic |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=Never Manage Alone |language=en}}</ref> He combines powerful brute force with nifty changes of pace, which allows him to expertly manoeuvre through tight spaces.<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":6">{{Cite web |title=Mateo Kovačić: Chelsea's Quintessential Midfield General |url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/mateo-kovacic-chelseas-quintessential-midfield-general/ |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=Breaking The Lines |date=5 July 2022 |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=":7">{{Cite web |title=Kovacic's style can take Man City to a new level |date=27 June 2023 |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/3526672 |access-date=2023-11-02 |publisher=Premier League |language=en}}</ref> He lies in the 97th percentile for players dribbled past per 90 minutes,<ref name=":6" /> preferring to charge beyond defenders to create chances from advanced positions.<ref name=":5" /><ref name=":7" /> Kovačić is highly proficient at what is known as "press resistance", the capacity to  out of trouble when under pressure from one or more opposition players, often via a [[Dribbling|dribble]] or clever [[Passing (association football)|pass]] around the corner.<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" /><ref name=":5" />

===Reception===
The Croatia under-17 manager, [[Martin Novoselac]], reportedly said of Kovačić, "I haven't seen a youngster with so much talent since the days of [[Robert Prosinečki]]," referring to his fast development and talent.<ref name="zidak"/><ref name="vahid"/> Kovačić revealed that precisely [[Robert Prosinečki|Prosinečki]] is the player he admired the most while growing up.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kovačić otkrio Talijanima koga je 'snimao' |url=http://www.tportal.hr/sport/nogomet/242330/Kovacic-otkrio-Talijanima-koga-je-volio-gledati.html |publisher=Tportal.hr |date=8 February 2013 |language=hr |access-date=12 May 2013 |archive-date=19 December 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219014846/http://www.tportal.hr/sport/nogomet/242330/Kovacic-otkrio-Talijanima-koga-je-volio-gledati.html |url-status=live }}</ref> His compatriot, [[Zvonimir Boban]], who played for [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] for over a decade, in an interview with [[Sky Italia]] in 2013 said, "He has talents that could make him even better than me, he is an incredibly serious professional for someone his age. Kovačić is a complete player. He is not a born regista but he is playing there now. He is a complete talent that can still grow&nbsp;— he has incredible potential."<ref>{{cite news |title=Inter snap up Kovacic and Kuzmanovic |url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/news/story/_/id/1320857/inter-snap-kovacic-kuzmanovic?cc=5739 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130216033450/http://soccernet.espn.go.com/news/story/_/id/1320857/inter-snap-kovacic-kuzmanovic?cc=5739 |url-status=dead |archive-date=16 February 2013 |date=31 January 2013 |website=ESPN Soccernet |access-date=3 February 2013 }}</ref> [[Giovanni Trapattoni|Trapattoni]] described him as "a mixture of [[Kaká]] and [[Clarence Seedorf]]", because of his style of play and technical characteristics.<ref>{{cite news |title='Kovacic is a mix of Kaka and Seedorf' – Trapattoni |url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/10/italy/2013/11/24/4428536/kovacic-is-a-mix-of-kaka-and-seedorf-trapattoni |date=24 November 2013 |work=Goal (website) |access-date=5 December 2013 |archive-date=30 November 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131130131720/http://www.goal.com/en/news/10/italy/2013/11/24/4428536/kovacic-is-a-mix-of-kaka-and-seedorf-trapattoni |url-status=live }}</ref> Long-time Inter captain [[Javier Zanetti]] stated that, with the exception of [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]], who had arrived to [[Inter Milan|Inter]] when he was 21, Kovačić was the most promising youngster he had seen in his 19 years at the club.<ref>{{cite web |title=Face to face: Javier Zanetti |url=http://www.worldsoccer.com/features/face-to-face-javier-zanetti |first=Jamie |last=Rainbow |date=12 August 2013 |publisher=WorldSoccer |access-date=1 February 2014 |archive-date=21 February 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221205239/http://www.worldsoccer.com/features/face-to-face-javier-zanetti/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

==Personal life==
Kovačić was born in [[Linz]], Austria, to [[Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian Croat]] parents Stipo and Ružica who had moved there from [[Zabrđe, Kotor Varoš|Zabrđe]]<ref>{{Cite web|date=5 July 2018|title="Vatreni" na bosanski pogon|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/255151-vatreni-na-bosanski-pogon|access-date=28 February 2021|website=Reprezentacija.ba|language=bs-BA|archive-date=2 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210602215857/https://reprezentacija.ba/255151-vatreni-na-bosanski-pogon|url-status=live}}</ref> ahead of the [[Yugoslav Wars]].<ref name="zidak" /><ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite web|date=10 June 2007|title=Nogometni wunderkind u Dinamu|url=https://www.jutarnji.hr/naslovnica/nogometni-wunderkind-u-dinamu-3780414|access-date=12 December 2020|website=Jutarnji list|language=hr-hr|archive-date=2 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210602214242/https://www.jutarnji.hr/naslovnica/nogometni-wunderkind-u-dinamu-3780414|url-status=live}}</ref> Kovačić is a [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] and attends church every Sunday.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mateo Kovačić: Hrvati, uzdajmo se u Boga! Dičimo se svojim i ne vrijeđajmo druge |url=http://www.zupa-svanastazija.com/novost/mateo-kovacic-hrvati-uzdajmo-se-u-boga-dicimo-se-svojim-i-ne-vrijedajmo-druge/582/ |access-date=22 June 2016 |archive-date=27 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327091621/http://www.zupa-svanastazija.com/novost/mateo-kovacic-hrvati-uzdajmo-se-u-boga-dicimo-se-svojim-i-ne-vrijedajmo-druge/582/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He speaks five languages: Croatian, German, English, Italian and Spanish.<ref>{{cite news |title=El vídeo que demuestra que Kovacic habla ¡5 idiomas! |date=7 December 2016 |work=Marca|location=Spain |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/real-madrid/2016/12/07/58474b82e5fdeaba688b464e.html |access-date=8 December 2016 |archive-date=27 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327102103/https://www.marca.com/futbol/real-madrid/2016/12/07/58474b82e5fdeaba688b464e.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

In 2017, Kovačić married his longtime girlfriend Izabel Andrijanić.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mateo Kovačić oženio djevojku Izabel, na svadbi i zvijezde Reala |date=17 June 2017 |publisher=Večernji list |url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/mateo-kovacic-ozenio-djevojku-izabel-na-svadbi-i-zvijezde-reala-1177259 |access-date=16 September 2019 |archive-date=10 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210310183148/https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/mateo-kovacic-ozenio-djevojku-izabel-na-svadbi-i-zvijezde-reala-1177259 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 12 October 2020, Andrijanić gave birth to their first child, a boy.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Kunić|first=Nikolina|date=13 October 2020|title=EKSKLUZIVNO Sve o prvorođenom sinu Izabel i Matea Kovačića|url=https://story.hr/Celebrity/a146512/EKSKLUZIVNO-Sve-o-prvorodjenom-sinu-Izabel-i-Matea-Kovacica.html|access-date=14 October 2020|website=Story|language=hr|archive-date=18 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201118040101/https://story.hr/Celebrity/a146512/EKSKLUZIVNO-Sve-o-prvorodjenom-sinu-Izabel-i-Matea-Kovacica.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=15 October 2020|title=Otkriveno kako su Mateo i Izabel Kovačić nazvali sina|url=https://www.index.hr/Magazin/clanak/otkriveno-kako-su-mateo-i-izabel-kovacic-nazvali-sina/2222116.aspx|website=Index.hr|language=hr|access-date=15 October 2020|archive-date=30 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130071242/https://www.index.hr/magazin/clanak/otkriveno-kako-su-mateo-i-izabel-kovacic-nazvali-sina/2222116.aspx|url-status=live}}</ref> The child was christened, with the first name Ivan, in July 2021, with [[Luka Modrić]] as his godfather.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Serdarević |first1=Neva |title=Mateo i Izabel Kovačić krstili su sinčića, Luka Modrić mu je kum |url=https://www.24sata.hr/show/mateo-i-izabel-kovacic-krstili-su-sincica-luka-modric-mu-je-kum-773226 |website=24sata |access-date=4 August 2021 |language=hr |date=12 July 2021 |archive-date=3 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803222655/https://www.24sata.hr/show/mateo-i-izabel-kovacic-krstili-su-sincica-luka-modric-mu-je-kum-773226 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2025, they had their daughter Luna.

